		<div class="post-3002 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-awesome category-festivals category-grief category-urbana" id="post-3002">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2013/04/05/r-i-p-roger-ebert/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to R.I.P. Roger Ebert">R.I.P. Roger Ebert</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>I am so grateful I got to meet Roger Ebert in 2009, when he screened <em>Sita Sings the Blues</em> at Ebertfest. He couldn&#8217;t speak then, but he stood onstage while his computer&#8217;s synthetic voice read his comments and looked intently in my eyes to make sure I was taking it in. He really wanted me to receive his gift, which was hard because it was so generous.</p>
<div id="attachment_3003" style="width: 593px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Nina+Roger_Ebertfest2009.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-3003" title="Nina+Roger_Ebertfest2009" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Nina+Roger_Ebertfest2009.jpg" alt="" width="583" height="479" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Roger Ebert and Nina Paley at Eberfest 2009. Photo by Chris Anderson</p></div>
<p>Here is his longer <a href="http://blogs.suntimes.com/ebert/2008/12/having_wonderful_time_wish_you.html" target="_blank">review of Sita Sings the Blues</a>, which brought many, many viewers to it.</p>
